The paper deals with efficient representations of query results and their computation, which is a core problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely category. The paper also involves hypergraphs and hypertree decompositions, which are topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses functional aggregate queries, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
